Pemex to Build Cogeneration Power Station in Mexico State of Nuevo Leon



Industry Segment: Power | Word Count: 307 Words
SUGAR LAND--December 29, 2015--Researched by Industrial Info Resources (Sugar Land, Texas)--Mexico's state-owned oil giant, Petroleos Mexicanos (Pemex) (Mexico City), has created a new subsidiary called PMX Cogeneracion, SAPI de CV to help build cogeneration power plants at its oil refineries, and has recently chosen Mitsui de Mexico, S de RL de CV (Mexico City) as a joint venture (JV) partner to help with the task.
Within this article: Details configuration and construction/completion dates for the 380-MW project.













