Press room > Press releases > Pemex's Board of Directors approved the start of operations of the productive state-owned subsidiaries E&P and Cogeneration and Services









                                                                                                                
	
	
			Pemex's Board of Directors approved the start of operations of the productive state-owned subsidiaries E&P and Cogeneration and Services
		

                                                                                                                












                                                                                                                                                        Press releases
                                                                                                                                                        








Press releasesActualmente seleccionadoPresentations









Compartir
                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                            





















					22/05/2015
					| 50 
					


Contenido de la páginaThe following appointments were approved
The Board of Directors of Petróleos Mexicanos (CAPEMEX) approved the start of operations of the newly created productive state-owned subsidiaries, Pemex Exploración y Producción (Pemex Exploration and Production) and Pemex Cogeneración y Servicios (Pemex Cogeneration and Services).
In addition, along with Pemex’s corporate reorganization process, the Board approved the appointment of corresponding directors, upon the  the proposal of the Director General:
In the case of E&P, a Management Committee was created, which will be formed by Juan Hinojosa Puebla, Director of Development and Production; José Antonio Escalera Alcocer, Director of Exploration, and Gustavo Hernández García, Director of Operations.
Hinojosa Puebla will preside the Management Committee as Executive Director.
On the other hand, Eleazar Gómez Zapata was appointed Director of Pemex Cogeneración y Servicios. Gómez Zapata acted as Deputy Director of Maintenance Coordination of the Corporate Direction of Operations, which transformed into Corporate Direction of Planning, Coordination and Performance.
In addition, Rodulfo Figueroa Alonso, who acted as Deputy Director of Planning of Pemex Gas and Basic Petrochemicals, was appointed as the new Corporate Director of Planning, Coordination and Performance.











