ovalí Jaime refinery. The refinery is owned by Pemex Refinación, a subsidiary of Pemex. The cogeneration plant will supply Pemex with electricity and steam, with excess power to be sold on the market. The goal is to have a power station that generates power in a competitive, steady and sustainable manner, thereby helping the Mexican government fulfill its commitment to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by around 50%. During the construction phase, this project should create 1,500 direct jobs.       Only BNamericas Subscribers Can Access This Information. Subscribe to BNamericas to gain better insight into project development and contract opportunities in Latin America.    Early-stage and under-development projects throughout the regionProject coverage focused on biggest investments in each country and sectorProject milestones highlighting planned and unplanned developmentsSales contacts within operators and contracted companiesAccess to experienced research staffRisk analysis of cost increases, scheduling conflicts and regulatory environment          Start a Free Trial   Already a subscriber? Please, login       This project profile is one of hundreds of projects being inputted, updated and researched daily, focusing on major milestones, associated companies and business contacts for active Electric Power. Including industry-specific information, insight and forecasts for Latin American business opportunities, Business News Americas also focuses on active companies and business and sales contacts , providing networking opportunities with leading executives Contact us today! Phone:+56 (2) 2941-0300       Milestones Log and News              Locked content   Dear visitor, this table includes insights that is only available for subscribers                   Related Companies    Need further information?        Name Sector Country Relation      Locked content   Project Owners     Locked content   Construction      Dear visitor, this table includes insights that is only av